Q. A Microsoft Azure Supercloud customer is defined as a customer who has purchased at least one product from every product category 
listed in the products table.

Write a query that identifies the customer IDs of these Supercloud customers.

A.
WITH cloud_data AS
(SELECT customer_id, 
COUNT(DISTINCT(p.product_category)) AS product_count
FROM customer_contracts c
INNER JOIN products p ON c.product_id = p.product_id
GROUP BY customer_id
)

SELECT customer_id
FROM cloud_data
WHERE product_count = (SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT product_category) FROM products)
;
